data.reddit:
27 year old Caucasian female 5’6” 205 pounds

History depression and PCOS

Current meds Prozac 20 mg daily and Spironolactone 50mg daily

Been feeling like this since 7am today, returned from Cancun Monday evening.


Seeking advice as many factors at play. Since May I’ve adopted a healthy low carb diet and daily exercise. Every time I’ve adjusted to low carb, I get muscle aches, some nausea and brain fog which I’ve always understood as normal and it passes despite some discomfort for a few days.

I just got back from a resort in Mexico and felt so gross and bloated I had all the sugary drinks and bad food there, but I felt fine while on vacation. Had a stressful flight and stressful day at work yesterday. I had virtually no carbs yesterday but lots of fat and protein and did my strenuous workout.

This am, still no carbs. I’m nauseous, achey, and have had foul diarrhea 3 times today. I haven’t even been able to get out of bed aside from the bathroom. Does this warrant an urgent care visit or wait to see if I’m detoxing the junk out? I was told this may be an electrolyte issue. I had some pickles and do feel slightly better to the point I can function a little better and do my laundry since I’m less achey.

Of note, my mom and sister who were with me on vacation feel great.
